660
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:10,900
Remember,

661
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:12,920
the real basic differential equations here

662
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,480
do not involve the vector potential.

663
00:26:14,980 --> 00:26:16,580
That means there's some sort

664
00:26:16,580 --> 00:26:18,180
of redundancy of the description,

665
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,460
because we can change the vector potential

666
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:24,380
without changing the physics.

667
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:25,920
And we can also think of

668
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:27,040
it as a kind of symmetry,

669
00:26:27,340 --> 00:26:30,520
a kind of symmetry of the system

670
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:35,700
where changing the vector potential in a certain way

671
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:38,120
has no influence on the motion.

672
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:39,340
It's a kind of symmetry.

673
00:26:39,460 --> 00:26:40,860
It's called gauge invariance,

674
00:26:41,439 --> 00:26:42,980
and here's the way it works.

675
00:26:49,820 --> 00:26:50,520
Let's take,

676
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:53,460
just to understand it,

677
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:57,740
let's focus on a particular component of del cross A.

678
00:26:57,980 --> 00:26:59,260
Let's say the z component.

679
00:27:01,180 --> 00:27:03,300
But all the other components work the same way.

680
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:05,180
What is the z component of del cross A?

681
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:08,780
It is derivative with respect to x,

682
00:27:08,980 --> 00:27:10,140
that means d by dx,

683
00:27:10,540 --> 00:27:13,430
of A y minus the derivative

684
00:27:13,430 --> 00:27:16,320
with respect to y of A x.

685
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:17,560
That's its definition.

686
00:27:19,340 --> 00:27:19,940
Now,

687
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,200
supposing I add,

688
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:25,680
I'll write it in vector notation

689
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,520
and then just explicitly in components,

690
00:27:27,660 --> 00:27:29,620
supposing I add to the vector potential

691
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:33,400
something which is itself a gradient.

692
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:36,940
I'm going to call it lambda,

693
00:27:36,940 --> 00:27:38,160
lambda of x.

694
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:39,000
What is a gradient?

695
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:42,420
A gradient simply means

696
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:45,260
the ith component,

697
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:47,840
we add to the ith component of A,

698
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:53,920
we add derivative with respect to x i of lambda.

699
00:27:54,680 --> 00:27:55,280
Now,

700
00:27:55,280 --> 00:27:56,160
lambda can be anything.

701
00:27:57,880 --> 00:28:01,340
The point is that changing A in this way

702
00:28:01,340 --> 00:28:03,360
doesn't change the curl of A.

703
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,960
Let's see why that is.

704
00:28:05,820 --> 00:28:08,600
Supposing I now recalculate the curl of A

705
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:11,440
after having introduced this extra term here.

706
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:14,440
For example,

707
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,920
let's take the x and y component.

708
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:20,880
A sub x will now have the

709
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:24,560
new term d by dx of lambda,

710
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:28,550
and A sub y will now have

711
00:28:28,550 --> 00:28:31,900
the new term d by dy of lambda.

712
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:34,980
Lambda of x means lambda

713
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,600
of x and y in general.

714
00:28:37,780 --> 00:28:38,260
Okay,

715
00:28:38,260 --> 00:28:38,800
x and y.

716
00:28:40,180 --> 00:28:41,260
Let's just leave it that way.

717
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:42,200
Okay,

718
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,520
what happens to the curl?

719
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:45,720
The curl gets another piece.

720
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:50,920
It gets a plus derivative with respect to x

721
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,740
of the new term in A y.

722
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:54,770
The new term in A y

723
00:28:54,770 --> 00:28:56,300
is d by dy of lambda.

724
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:02,480
But then we have to correct this term.

725
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:05,310
That's minus d by dy of

726
00:29:05,310 --> 00:29:08,140
the new term in A x.

727
00:29:08,660 --> 00:29:10,910
The new term in A x is

728
00:29:10,910 --> 00:29:13,160
derivative with respect to x of lambda.

729
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:16,880
Well,

730
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,400
these are exactly the same thing.

731
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:19,580
d by dx,

732
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:22,300
d by dy of lambda is exactly the same thing

733
00:29:22,300 --> 00:29:22,940
as d by dy,

734
00:29:22,940 --> 00:29:23,680
d by dx.

735
00:29:23,940 --> 00:29:27,120
The order of operations of derivatives is immaterial.

736
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:31,600
And so by adding the gradient of a scalar,

737
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:33,460
to a vector,

738
00:29:33,460 --> 00:29:35,400
it does not change its curl.

739
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:38,280
Another way to say it

740
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:40,420
is the gradient of a scalar

741
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,480
doesn't have a curl.

742
00:29:43,140 --> 00:29:44,460
It's curl-free.

743
00:29:49,339 --> 00:29:49,979
So,

744
00:29:49,979 --> 00:29:51,960
by adding to the vector potential

745
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:54,380
the gradient of a scalar,

746
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,620
we change the vector potential,

747
00:29:56,940 --> 00:29:58,780
we change the Lagrangian,

748
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:02,340
but we don't change the equation of

749
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:02,700
motion.

750
00:30:03,940 --> 00:30:05,540
I will remind you,

751
00:30:05,540 --> 00:30:06,760
in some ways in your notes,

752
00:30:06,980 --> 00:30:08,440
I worked out,

753
00:30:09,060 --> 00:30:09,580
well,

754
00:30:09,580 --> 00:30:10,360
maybe we should do it.

755
00:30:10,420 --> 00:30:11,260
Let's do it over again.

756
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:14,220
Just to keep the lecture self-contained.

